{"subjectName":"Business","subjectDescription":"Discover a full suite of online business courses that will allow you to make better business decisions and succeed in today's competitive business world. Our courses provide a rich learning experience that will allow you to develop critical business skills in areas such as business... Read more...","subjectBg":"https://cdn01.alison-static.net/search/header-img/business.jpg","resumeLink":"https://alison.com/resume/courses/5098","title":"Introduction to Rapid Business Improvement","totalEnrolled":"291","courseIncludes":["1.5-3 Hours of Learning","CPD Accreditation","Final Assessment"],"headline":"Learn how to implement rapid business improvement and reap its benefits in this free online business management course.","description":"Business ‘process improvement’ includes identifying issues, mapping out processes, finding the root cause and solution to problems and implementing them to improve organisational efficiency. What if you could achieve all this within a month? In this course, we’ll introduce you to rapid business improvement techniques and show you how to use them to streamline processes and eliminate waste and errors in your company within a month.","courseOutcomes":["Define ‘rapid business improvement’ ...","Outline its basics and benefits ...","Identify the projects where a rapid ...","Summarise the 8-step process of deli...","Define ‘rapid business improvement’ (RBI)","Outline its basics and benefits","Identify the projects where a rapid business improvement initiative is needed","Summarise the 8-step process of delivering rapid business improvement","Explain the use of business improvement tools like Fishbone, ‘5-Whys’ or FMEA","Identify when to employ gap and impact analysis","Outline the points to cover while building a case presentation","Define ‘rapid business improvement’ ...","Outline its basics and benefits ...","Identify the projects where a rapid ...","Summarise the 8-step process of deli...","Define ‘rapid business improvement’ (RBI)","Outline its basics and benefits","Identify the projects where a rapid business improvement initiative is needed","Summarise the 8-step process of delivering rapid business improvement","Explain the use of business improvement tools like Fishbone, ‘5-Whys’ or FMEA","Identify when to employ gap and impact analysis","Outline the points to cover while building a case presentation"],"courseDescription":"<p>Optimising business operations through efficient process improvement is one of the critical factors in an organisation's continued success in today's changing markets. Delivering effective business improvement the traditional way impacts only a fragment of the end-to-end business process and takes a long time. What if you have a complex problem that requires immediate attention? You will need to employ a practical rapid business improvement (RBI) technique to solve such a problem. RBI involves a small team devoting 100% of their time over three to five days to analyse and improve a defined targeted issue or process. But employing this business methodology without a clear direction can create a disorganised mess that wastes time and effort. In this course, we will teach you how to use traditional business improvement methodologies to deliver rapid improvements to business processes within a month.</p><p>The course introduces you to the fundamentals of rapid business improvement, its benefits and its purpose. The success or failure of any improvement methodology depends on how it is planned. We will guide you through the stage of identifying a problem in a process and forming a team capable of delivering impactful solutions to the problem within a week. You'll learn how to map a process, collect data, identify the value and non-value-add steps and find the root cause for both big and small problems in the process. We'll help you understand the ins and outs of finding effective solutions, building a case presentation and selling it to stakeholders. In addition, we will walk you through the 8-step process for delivering a successful RBI and provide a wealth of resources and tools for you to use at each stage.</p><p>This course is ideal if you are short on time or want to quickly deliver business improvement. Your instructor, Robert Chapman, uses real-life case studies to help you understand the course better. Delivering business improvement effectively is a challenge for many organisations so they simply don't bother - at a high cost to them! This course will teach you how to do it quickly and effectively, giving you an edge in your career. Managers, business improvement professionals, entrepreneurs and team leaders can use process improvement to reduce waste and inefficiency in the workplace. There are no prerequisites for this course so enrol today and take that next step in your career.</p><a href=\"https://alison.com/resume/courses/5098\" class=\"l-but course_btn\">Start Course Now</a>","certificateDetail":"<p> All Alison courses are free to enrol study and complete. To successfully complete this <span class=\"course-type\">certificate</span> course and become an Alison Graduate, you need to achieve 80% or higher in each course assessment. Once you have completed this <span class=\"course-type\">certificate</span> course, you have the option to acquire an official Diploma, which is a great way to share your achievement with the world. </p><div class=\"l-list l-list--tick\"><h6>Your Alison <span class=\"course-type\">certificate</span> is:</h6><ul><li>Ideal for sharing with potential employers</li><li>Include it in your CV, professional social media profiles and job applications.</li><li>An indication of your commitment to continuously learn, upskill &amp; achieve high results.</li><li>An incentive for you to continue empowering yourself through lifelong learning.</li></ul></div><hr><div class=\"l-flex l-flex--even\"><div class=\"l-list l-list--bullet\"><h6>Alison offers <span class=\"l-list__