ary</b></h4></div><div class=\"caption ng-binding\"></div></li><li id=\"iWzQs\" data-space=\"\" full-editor=\"\" class=\"component list paragraph, listed   ui-resizable\"><div class=\"asset-header ng-binding\"></div><div ng-paste=\"removeFormat($event, item.title)\" class=\"editable p-asset ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-valid ng-binding ng-scope ng-not-empty None\">The key contents covered in the module are the following: </div><div class=\"caption ng-binding\"></div></li><li id=\"uIjap\" data-space=\"\" full-editor=\"\" class=\"component list list-item, listed selected-class   ui-resizable border\"><div class=\"asset-header ng-binding\"></div><div ng-paste=\"removeFormat($event, item.title)\" class=\"list-item editable ng-pristine ng-valid ng-binding ng-scope ng-not-empty None ng-touched\"><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"\">Rapid business improvement is a key technique used when the issues in a process(es) are known and need to be dealt with quickly, usually in under a month.</li><li class=\"\">Rapid business improvement (RBI) process is a structured 8-step/8-day approach.</li><li class=\"\">The 8 steps are: plan adequately whilst analysing all data available, map out the key process(es) affected by the issue(s) identified, root cause analysis (RCA) of the issues, identify the potential and then chosen solutions, build your buy-in presentation and then deliver it, implement your chosen solutions before continuously reviewing the outcome and outputs from the newly deployed process(es).</li><li class=\"\">The case presentation should highlight the long-term impact of not doing anything and the long-term benefit of actually doing something.</li><li class=\"\">It is better to use the Fishbone diagram method to root cause the big issues and the 5 – Whys diagram to root cause the smaller issues being faced in a process.</li><li class=\"\">The benefits of RBI include closing out a project in a quicker time and low cost. It is an approach to getting buy-in from key leads and aids in the personal and professional development of the team.</li><li class=\"\">The key to successful RBI is quantifying the benefits before, during and after implementation of the improvements and keeping stakeholders engaged and up to date throughout the process.</li></ul></div><div class=\"caption ng-binding\"></div></li></ul>\n"]}